le·thar·gic
/ləˈTHärjik/
Learn to pronounce
adjective
adjective: lethargic
  1. affected by lethargy; sluggish and apathetic.
    "I felt tired and a little lethargic"
    amusement
    Informal
    the state or experience of finding something funny.
